{"questionId":"14292675","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;defined for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;The derivative of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math>&nbsp;is such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, for all&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>\n<p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;be&nbsp;e the region enclosed by the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, the graph of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math>, the line&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and the line&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;The area of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>21</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use either the quotient or product rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correctly applying chain rule to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;and <em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;for everything else correct.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>6</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>60</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>72</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:30px;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14292675","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ1.9a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that f'x=122-5x2x2+24.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product 